## 🔴 Critical Vulnerabilities

### VULN-01: All Legacy Admin Routes Are Completely Unprotected

> [!CAUTION]
> **CVSS: 9.8 (Critical)** — Any anonymous user can call ALL `/api/admin/*` endpoints without any authentication.

**Affected routes (13 endpoints):**
```
GET  /api/admin/exams              ← List all exams
POST /api/admin/create-exam        ← Create exams
POST /api/admin/upload-exam-pdf    ← Upload question papers
POST /api/admin/publish-exam       ← Publish exams
POST /api/admin/unpublish-exam     ← Unpublish exams
DELETE /api/admin/exam/{code}      ← Delete exams
PUT  /api/admin/exam/{code}        ← Modify exams
POST /api/admin/register-student-face ← Register face embeddings
GET  /api/admin/dashboard/stats    ← View stats
GET  /api/admin/activity           ← View audit logs
GET  /api/admin/submissions        ← View all submissions
GET  /api/admin/students-for-scoring ← View all students
POST /api/admin/score              ← Modify student scores
GET  /api/admin/answers/{id}       ← View student answers
GET  /api/admin/answers/{id}/download ← Download answers
```

**Exploit:** `curl http://localhost:4000/api/admin/exams` — returns all exams, no auth needed.

**Root cause:** Legacy `/api/admin/login` only verifies credentials and returns `{authenticated: true}` — it does NOT issue a JWT token, so there's nothing to validate on subsequent requests.

