### VULN-02: Plaintext Password Fallback

> [!CAUTION]
> **CVSS: 9.1 (Critical)** — [verify_password()](file:///d:/mindkraft/Team-A-Frontend/Team-A-Backend/Team-A-Backend/app/security.py#15-24) falls back to **plaintext comparison** for non-bcrypt passwords.

**File:** [security.py:23](file:///d:/mindkraft/Team-A-Frontend/Team-A-Backend/Team-A-Backend/app/security.py#L23)
```python
return stored_value == password  # ← Plaintext comparison!
```

Any password stored without the `$2` bcrypt prefix is compared as raw plaintext. The seed script stores `passwordHash: 'student123'` — this means student login with `student123` will succeed via plaintext comparison.

---

### VULN-03: Student Auth is Client-Side Only (Trivially Bypassable)

> [!CAUTION]
> **CVSS: 8.5 (High)** — Student-protected routes only check `sessionStorage` in the browser. Zero server-side verification.

**File:** [ProtectedRoute.tsx:50-52](file:///d:/mindkraft/Team-A-Frontend/Team-A-Frontend/src/components/ProtectedRoute.tsx#L50-L52)
```typescript
const studentAuth =
    sessionStorage.getItem('studentAuth') === 'true' ||
    Boolean(sessionStorage.getItem('studentId'));
```

**Exploit:** Open browser console → `sessionStorage.setItem('studentAuth', 'true')` → access any student page. No backend verification whatsoever.

Additionally, student API endpoints (`/api/student/*`) have **no auth middleware** — any anonymous HTTP client can call them.

---

### VULN-04: NoSQL Injection via Raw dict Bodies

> [!WARNING]
> **CVSS: 8.2 (High)** — All routes accept `body: dict[str, Any]` with no validation. MongoDB operators can be injected.

**Example attack on admin login:**
```json
POST /api/admin/login
{
  "username": {"$gt": ""},
  "password": {"$gt": ""}
}
```

Since PyMongo passes these directly to `find_one()`, MongoDB operators like `$gt`, `$ne`, `$regex` can bypass authentication or extract data.

---

### VULN-05: Stack Traces Leaked to Clients

> [!WARNING]
> **CVSS: 5.3 (Medium)** — The generic exception handler returns `str(exc)` which exposes internal details.

**File:** [main.py:70-72](file:///d:/mindkraft/Team-A-Frontend/Team-A-Backend/Team-A-Backend/app/main.py#L70-L72)
```python
async def generic_exception_handler(_request, exc):
    return JSONResponse(status_code=500, content={"error": str(exc), "message": str(exc)})
```

This leaks file paths, database queries, and stack traces to attackers.

