## 🟠 High Vulnerabilities

### VULN-06: No Rate Limiting on Any Endpoint

- Face recognition can be brute-forced with all possible embeddings
- Admin login can be brute-forced
- No throttling on API calls → easy DoS

### VULN-07: Face Auth Thresholds Too Low

Cosine similarity threshold lowered from `0.85` to `0.75` and Euclidean from `0.55` to `0.70`. The `OR` condition makes it worse — either threshold passing is enough. This increases false positive acceptance rate.

### VULN-08: No Liveness Detection Enforcement

The README mentions liveness detection, but the backend does zero liveness verification. A printed photo or screen showing a face will pass verification.

### VULN-09: JWT Secret Hardcoded in Source

**File:** [config.py:11](file:///d:/mindkraft/Team-A-Frontend/Team-A-Backend/Team-A-Backend/app/config.py#L11)
```python
jwt_secret: str = "vox-local-dev-secret-change-this"
```

Docker Compose uses `vox-docker-dev-secret-change-this`. Both are guessable defaults.

### VULN-10: Admin Legacy Login Has No JWT — Sessions Are Stateless

The `/api/admin/login` endpoint returns `{authenticated: true}` but **no token**. The frontend sets `sessionStorage.setItem('adminAuth', 'true')` — same trivial bypass as students.

### VULN-11: Face Embeddings Stored/Transmitted Unencrypted

128-dimensional face embeddings are biometric data. They're stored in MongoDB without encryption and transmitted over HTTP in plain JSON.

### VULN-12: MongoDB Has No Authentication

Docker Compose runs MongoDB without `MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_USERNAME`/`MONGO_INITDB_ROOT_PASSWORD`. Anyone with network access can connect directly.

---

## 🟡 Medium Vulnerabilities

### VULN-13: Docker Runs as Root

Both backend and frontend containers run as root user — container escape gives full host access.

### VULN-14: No Request Size Limits on Backend

No `max_body_size` on FastAPI — an attacker can send multi-GB payloads to crash the server.

### VULN-15: Exam Questions Accessible Without Auth

`GET /api/student/exams` and `GET /api/student/exam/{code}` return full exam questions without any authentication.

